      </div>
    </div>

    <p>The key insight about berberine is that it does not simply affect one pathway — it modulates multiple metabolic systems simultaneously. This explains why clinical research shows benefits across seemingly unrelated conditions like diabetes, high cholesterol, gut dysbiosis, and fatty liver. They are all connected through metabolic dysfunction, and berberine addresses the shared underlying mechanism through AMPK activation.</p>

