    <!-- SECTION 5: CORRECT DOSAGE -->
    <h2>Correct Berberine Dosage by Condition</h2>

    <p>Dosage is one of the most critical factors in berberine supplementation. Under-dosing produces negligible effects, while the correct dose — taken at the right time — produces the clinical benefits documented in research. The standard protocol used in the majority of successful clinical trials is 500mg taken 2-3 times daily with meals, for a total daily intake of 1,000-1,500mg.</p>

    <p>Taking berberine with meals serves two purposes: it improves absorption (food slows gastric transit, giving the intestines more time to absorb berberine) and it reduces the GI side effects that occur when berberine is taken on an empty stomach. Splitting the dose across meals also maintains more consistent blood levels throughout the day, which is important because berberine has a relatively short half-life of approximately 4-6 hours.</p>

