            <td>Additive blood sugar lowering — increased hypoglycemia risk</td>
            <td>High — requires physician monitoring</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Insulin and sulfonylureas</strong></td>
            <td>Additive blood sugar lowering — can cause severe hypoglycemia</td>
            <td>High — do not combine without MD</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="hl">
            <td><strong>Blood thinners (warfarin)</strong></td>
            <td>Berberine may inhibit CYP enzymes that metabolize warfarin, increasing bleeding risk</td>
            <td>High — requires INR monitoring</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Cyclosporine</strong></td>
            <td>Berberine increases cyclosporine blood levels by inhibiting CYP3A4</td>
            <td>High — can cause cyclosporine toxicity</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="hl">
            <td><strong>Antihypertensives</strong></td>
            <td>Additive blood pressure lowering</td>
            <td>Moderate — monitor blood pressure</td>
          </tr>
