            <td>Additive QT prolongation risk</td>
            <td>Moderate — avoid concurrent use</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Thyroid medications (levothyroxine)</strong></td>
            <td>Berberine may reduce absorption</td>
            <td>Low-Moderate — separate by 2+ hours</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <p>If you take any prescription medications, consult your physician or pharmacist before starting berberine. The CYP enzyme inhibition is the most concerning interaction because it can affect the blood levels of many drugs beyond those listed above. A pharmacist can perform a comprehensive drug interaction check for your specific medication list.</p>

