    <div class="verdict">
      <h3>The Evidence-Based Verdict: What Is Berberine Good For?</h3>
      <p>Berberine is one of the most thoroughly researched natural compounds in modern pharmacology, with over 4,500 published studies supporting benefits across 9 major health areas. The strongest evidence supports its use for blood sugar regulation (comparable to metformin in clinical trials), cholesterol management (20-25% LDL reduction through a unique mechanism), and metabolic health through AMPK and GLP-1 activation. It also shows clinically meaningful benefits for PCOS, NAFLD, gut health, and inflammation.</p>
      <p>At the standard dose of 500mg taken 2-3 times daily with meals, berberine is well-tolerated by most adults with GI side effects being the most common complaint. It is not appropriate for pregnant or breastfeeding women, children, or people with severe liver disease. Anyone taking prescription medications — especially metformin, insulin, blood thinners, or cyclosporine — must consult a physician before adding berberine. When used correctly, berberine represents a powerful, evidence-backed addition to a metabolic health regimen.</p>
